snippet.textDisplay:
Why not make a video w/out tearing something up completely or ruining it intentionally.... (you can give used trucks to views and write off in taxes, make someone happy that could never afford a truck like that, think about others and donate your old trucks to people that are in need of one to start a business etc. you could change someone’s life for the better if you would think about others OUTSIDE family and friends don’t act like a on pills Rich kid w/out sense, just to get a lol from another rich kid watching your vid... I’m not hating I am glad you’re to support yourself and have atleast a few employees your able to pay hopefully a good livable wage while they are blessed to have a pretty cool job. You are for the most part doing all the right things, but I don’t think you will lose ANY views if you didn’t completely ruin the trucks. Trash them for views I get it, but at least don’t ruin it. Think about others outside your circle of friends and family that could CHANGE A PERSONS LIFE FOR THE BETTER FOREVER. so many people wanting to start ones own business who have ALL the tools even a trailer but can’t afford a big enough truck that is reliable to get them to and from the job site..
I have a f-150 that won’t pull my trailers, thankfully I was able to by a used f-350(not a duly) to pull those trailer to and from the work site.. if I was not able to buy that truck my business would have suffered greatly, point is think about donating those trucks to people you see trying hard to better one’s life and post the video on your channel, most likely the kids that watch your channel will think that’s lame but you will be respected by the parents and other mature people.( again I am not downing your or any of your videos, I understand you do it for views, but views won’t change much if you totally ruin a truck with a excavator( not sure kids watch to see that part nor would that make or break your video views)... stay safe and remember your blessed, it’s never to early to give some back. Good karma, remember karma, do good to others and it will come back around.
